The [[morphemes]] '''terat(o)-''' and '''pelor(o)-''' in [[scientific]] words and names mean "[[monster]]". They came from [[Greek language|Greek]]. Usually:-
*''terato-'' means "monster" in the sense of [[teratology|something abnormal]].
*''peloro-'' means "monster" in the popular sense of "something huge".
But there are exceptions, for example:-
*[[Teratornis]] = "monster bird" is an extinct species of [[condor]] with wingspan 12 [[feet]].
*[[Terataspis]] = "monster shield" is a very big species of [[trilobite]].

